\{x_n\}_{n=1}^{\infty}
\{y_n\}_{n=1}^{\infty}
  \limsup x_n +\liminf y_n \le \limsup\,(x_n+y_n). 
\text{Fix } K>1. \text{ Let }L=\inf_{1\le i \le k}y_i
k \rightarrow \infty
 \sup_{1 \le i \le k}(x_i+y_i)\ge \sup_{1\le i \le k}(x_i+L)=L+\sup_{1\le i \le k}(x_i) =  \inf_{1\le i \le k}(y_i)+\sup_{1\le i \le k}(x_i). 
\limsup (x_n+y_n) = \lim_{n\to\infty} \left(\sup_{k>n}(x_k+y_k)\right) \leq  \lim_{n\to\infty}\left(\sup_{k>n}x_k+\sup_{k>n}y_k\right)=\\=\limsup(x_n)+\limsup (y_n)
\sup (a+b) \leq \sup (a) + \sup (b)
